cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual attention prediction and benchmarking existing models on a new dataset. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the capabilities of deep learning models in capturing the inherent mechanism of human visual attention. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of different models on a new dataset. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the capabilities of deep models in memorizing and predicting specific visual patterns. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the feasibility and key issues of predicting visual attention on the sun, which has implications for human-computer interaction.
